FIVE-YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY

Devro, Inc. has had an excellent record for preventing accidental releases over the last five years. Due to the effective release prevention policies, there have been no accidental release of ammonia of reportable quantities during the last five years.



EMERGENCY ACTION PLAN

The site has a written emergency action plan to deal with the accidental release of the covered process chemical, anhydrous ammonia, and other hazardous substances. The emergency action plan has been coordinated with local emergency response personnel. The plan contains the aspects of emergency response including adequate first aid and medical treatment, evacuations, and notification of the local emergency response groups, and the public. Devro will evacuate in the event of an emergency accidental release of anhydrous ammonia. 



